					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The end of this inscription is lost. It seems to record a gift, by <hi rend="bold">Perumāṉ Vāmaṉaṉ of Tiruvēṭpūr</hi> in Kavira-nāḍu a subdivision of Valla-nāḍu, of one <hi rend="italic">tuḷaippoṉ (kaḻañju)</hi> with the annual interest on which an offering was to be made to god Gōkarṇattu-Mahādēva, on the day of Uttiram evidently in Paṅguṉi month. This is evidently an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> (No. 73, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ins.</hi> Texts).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
